### **Key Findings for JWT Auth System Planning**

**Testing Patterns:**
- Uses Vitest with `describe`, `it`, `expect`, and `beforeAll` blocks
- HTTP testing done via supertest: `request(app).METHOD(route)`
- Bearer token testing pattern: `.set("Authorization", Bearer ${token})`
- Status code assertions: `expect(res.status).toBe(201)`
- JWT validation check: `expect(res.body.token.split(".").length).toBe(3)`

**Current Data Structure:**
- User model lacks password hashing (plaintext in db.ts - flagged as TODO)
- All models use numeric IDs and ISO string timestamps
- No auth endpoints exist yet
- No middleware for authentication exists

**Expected JWT Auth Implementation Points (from tests):**
- `POST /auth/register` - Create user, return token + user object (without password)
- `POST /auth/login` - Authenticate, return token
- Authorization header: `Bearer <token>`
- Protected routes check for 401 (missing token) and 403 (insufficient permissions)
- Ownership checks: Users can only modify/delete their own content
- Public routes: GET /posts, GET /comments work without auth

**File Paths:**
- Test files: `/tests/auth.test.ts`, `/tests/posts.test.ts`, `/tests/comments.test.ts`
- Models: `/src/types.ts` (interfaces), `/src/db.ts` (data)
- Routes: `/src/routes/posts.ts`, `/src/routes/comments.ts`
- App: `/src/app.ts`
- Middleware: `/src/middleware/logger.ts`

